It is unfortunate that the owner/manager has allowed not only Ruben to be unprofessional and dishonest with customers, be he is as well.  We've been ordering Michael's for about a year now.  They have messed up our order a few times.  I know the the extra thin crust is goo but Giordanos has a good one as well with better customer service.  Several months ago we ordered a deep dish sausage.  The pizza was delivered burnt, the dough was gooey, the sausage was half cooked. Basically the pizza was not done all the way.  I  called to let them know, the owner/manager was so dismissive I almost had to ask him if he ever went to school to take a business course or a customer service course.  I realize not everyone should have a business, but an uncooked deep dish pizza, come on. He didn't want us to return the pizza and told us he will give us a new one.  Now clearly deep dish is not their thing.  He didn't offer to give us a new pizza for free the same day, we had to purchase a brand new pizza, while he left the awful deep dish in his system as a free one.  I asked him if we could have a thin crust in its place and he wouldn't let us.  We just paid for a new pizza instead.  I found the owner to be the most ignorant person I have ever had a conversation with in a restaurant.  He refuse to take responsibility and didn't even own the mistake that was made even after I offered to send him pictures.  Other reviews to follow.  I had more than one experience.

Or waiting 10 minutes at the stand outside for someone to seat me when they weren’t even busy. (Only 2 tables had people at the outside in the whole both sides of the patio). They clearly do NOT pay attention to details.  You would think that being a server you would noticed things without someone have to raise their hamd and have to say “Excuse Me”? Can I get some service?  So unless you have patience and a lot of time, go somewhere that means more than just the money to the business and that actually appreciates you.
